I would give this 3.5 stars if I could, saving 4 stars for the truly exceptional. This recipe is delicious and so simple. I used two 6-oz jars from Trader Joe's (one in water, one in olive oil) and loved how it came out. The second time I used two cans in water and that was good as well. Chopping all the ingredients to almost a mince fooled my olive- and onion-hating boyfriend, who had seconds. I just bought tuna to make this a third time-- it's such a good staple lunch dish as a sandwich or salad.

