Rating: 4
This recipe was soo good. I used tablespoons each of the red wine vinegar an olive oil - I used a garlic infused olive oil because the flavour is more subtle. With so many flavours you don't need much dressing and it doesn't need to be strong. The oranges, onion and olives play off one another really nicely while the parsley keeps it all fresh. This is the ultimate dinner salad. I doubled the tuna to make it really filling but it wasn't necessary. Try it!!

